Black moves first.
A move consists of sliding a piece along 8 directions (queen-like) to any free square.
After a piece moves, its origin square becomes impassable.
The game ends when neither player has a legal move.
The player with the higher score (number of moves made) wins. Draw if equal.
Input tensor: 193 dimensions.
- 0:63: Black piece positions (bitboard)
- 64:127: White piece positions (bitboard)
- 128:191: Impassable squares (bitboard)
- 192: Turn (0=Black, 1=White)

Output: 3 classes (0: Black wins, 1: Draw, 2: White wins).
Network: Linear -> Clamp -> Linear -> Clamp -> Linear(3).
We need to output a vector of size MAPPED_DIM (32-128), normalized to [0, 1].
The mapping must be efficiently implementable in C++ with bitboard ops.
