Boundary check: `r, c = divmod(sq, 8)`.
If `sq` is e.g. 7 (h1), `d=1` -> `sq=8`. `divmod(8,8) = (1,0)`. `r=1, c=0`. Valid.
If `sq` is 63 (h8), `d=1` -> `sq=64`. `divmod(64,8) = (8,0)`. `r=8`. Invalid. Break.
If `sq` is 7 (h1), `d=-1` -> `sq=6`. `divmod(6,8) = (0,6)`. Valid.
If `sq` is 0 (a1), `d=-1` -> `sq=-1`. `divmod(-1,8) = (-1, 7)`. `r=-1`. Invalid. Break.
So boundary check works.

